Text.string: I appreciate you talking to me, but don't you have a universe to save?
Typhon's waiting for you—we can talk later.
I'd love to continue the tour, but you should go talk to Typhon.
I never met Troy or Tyreen. All I know is that they make Typhon sad.
Like I always say, if you have to live in hell, make it comfortable!
Now that you know about Typhon's children, don't think less of my master. He's a good guy.
He's dead... I can't believe it. Now I'm stuck with Grouse forever!
Now that Typhon's gone, it's doesn't feel like home anymore.
So, what are you gonna do now?
You did it! You saved the galaxy! That took chutzpah!
You're back! And the universe is still here! Yay!
Thanks for comin' by! Me and Grouse are doing fine here. Like Typhon always said, “when life hands you crap, make a turd sandwich!” He was weird, huh?
Maybe I should follow in Typhon's footsteps and become a turd farmer! Lots of turds around here. I'm looking at one! Haha, just kidding!
I'm working on a song about you. But nothing rhymes with “tuchus”!
I should probably be doing my chores.
Caves are dirty! I wish I could live in a closet like the bots on Promethea.
Some of my ancestors were explorers!
Sometimes, when I'm alone, I talk to myself. Is that okay?
I'm not allowed to use guns! But I would love to clean them. So many hands, trigger-fingers sweating all the time. And don't get me started on the blood and viscera! Grody.
Seeing you makes me sad.||—I'll get over it.
It's the hero of the galaxy!
What was I doing? Oh yeah!
[humming] No wait, that's—that's not how it goes. It's, uh...
I was just thinking about how cool you are!
You still in the middle of something?
